{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"body":"PLAN-REVIEW REMEDIATION (Round-11, 2026-06-29) — disposition of the 1 BLOCK + 15 advisory + 4 dropped findings (see session_log a7e2-381c-6dc6-4d0c for the analysis).\n\nRESOLVED — BLOCK (discriminates_novelty bar unspecified): the bar is now concrete in the framework's own idiom — a per-case 0.5-midpoint discriminator gated by gate:at_least(2)/epochs:3 + coverage_threshold:0.8 on ≥3 labeled novel/carryover pairs (NOT an invented AUC/F1). Specified on the epic 'Defaults & calibration' + AC, and on child 150b. Crucially separates THREE conflated numbers: runtime T_novel=0.7 (droppable-if-novel), eval floor 0.5 (per-case midpoint), eval bar at_least(2)/coverage 0.8 (scorer proven). cc5b carries an explicit evidence-gate precondition: drop rule inert until 150b clears the bar.\n\nRESOLVED — child title/body swaps (G4 critical x2): the bodies were rotated. ec89 now matches its title (task-4 remediation-mode gate: freshness window + preconditions + wiring), 3689 now matches its title (task-5 impact-prompt tightening) and no longer duplicates 4cb9's docs+tests scope. Deps were already correct per task numbering (cc5b→150b; ec89→e344; 4cb9→cc5b+ec89), so the dep graph is coherent post-swap.\n\nRESOLVED — ownership gaps (G3): T_novel default + priority-floor derivation now explicitly owned by cc5b; sidecar-write of DROPPED novel findings now an explicit cc5b AC; freshness-window/preconditions owned by ec89 (cc5b consumes its decision, no duplication).\n\nRESOLVED — novelty sub-answer set + scoring arithmetic (T8 critical): defined on 150b + epic — factual matches-prior questions, novelty = 1 − mean(matches-prior), yes/insufficient/no ordinal map.\n\nRESOLVED — fallback for failed/malformed novelty sub-call (T8): fail-safe novelty=0.0 (carryover, never dropped) on 150b.\n\nRESOLVED — code-change detection mechanism (G6): deterministic verified_at_sha equality (prior manifest vs current run) — reuses the signed snapshot ref, no new diff machinery (ec89 + epic).\n\nRESOLVED — default-on rollout risk (T4): config key flipped to default-OFF for v1 with an expand-contract rollout (ship off → validate → flip), on ec89 + epic + cc5b.\n\nNOTED (G6 advisory, kept as-is with justification): 'why an LLM novelty sub-call vs a deterministic norm_id fingerprint' — the norm_id fingerprint is an EXACT-match key (same normalized finding); novelty must catch SUBSTANTIVELY-same findings reworded across a plan edit (a fingerprint would miss a re-phrased carryover and let it through as novel), so the LLM matches-prior sub-call is the right tool. The independence invariant is still enforced structurally (separate sub-call). T_novel=0.7 rationale = house precision-first 0.70 standard, explicitly tunable + corpus-calibratable post-dogfood."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1782766248891007001,"uuid":"81ef1f88-e1dc-4532-92c7-0a3cfb4dc79f"}